The paper deals with submodular function minimization, which is a problem in discrete optimization theory. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the relevance of submodular minimization for various branches of mathematics, computer science, and economics, which could indicate that it belongs to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.OC (Optimization and Control) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a quantum algorithm, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category, as quantum computing is becoming increasingly relevant in this field.
